<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="127" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d127">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/416.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador to
                                        Japan</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The Minister for Foreign Affairs today inquired whether participation
                                if granted would place Japan in a position superior to an ordinary
                                bondholder. He said that Japan is greatly concerned in the Chinese
                                currency reform, especially as to the purposes of the Manchurian
                                allotment.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">O’Brien</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>